      <li>The African elephant is the largest land animal, with males weighing up to 6,000 kilograms (13,000 pounds).</li>
      <li>The blue whale is the largest animal ever known to have existed, reaching lengths of over 30 meters (98 feet).</li>
      <li>The Bengal tiger is the largest tiger subspecies and is found primarily in the Indian subcontinent.</li>
      <li>The monarch butterfly undergoes a long-distance migration, traveling thousands of kilometers to overwinter in specific sites.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="nature_card_item">
    <h2><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weather" target="_blank">Weather</a></h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Tornadoes are rapidly rotating columns of air that are often associated with severe thunderstorms.</li>
      <li>Lightning is a discharge of electricity that occurs during thunderstorms, often accompanied by thunder.</li>
      <li>Hurricanes, also known as typhoons or cyclones, are large tropical storms characterized by strong winds and heavy rainfall.</li>
      <li>The formation of rainbows is caused by the refraction, reflection, and dispersion of sunlight in water droplets.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
